[Student "S"]
{NORTH has 11 points and she should pass.

SOUTH has a minimum 1\H opening, 13 points and five trumps.

NORTH, with 4-card trump support, jumps to 3\H. 
(This is called a Limit Raise.)

A Limit Raise is an invitational bid, but SOUTH can add and he knows the total points will 
be either 24 or 25. So he passes 3\H.}

